==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murrain
<hw>Mur"rain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>moreine</ets>, OF. <ets>morine</ets>, fr. OF. <ets>morir</ets>,
<ets>murir</ets>, 8die, L. <ets>mori</ets>, <ets>moriri</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>An infectious and fatal disease among
cattle.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>A murrain on you</b></col>, <cd>may you be afflicted with
a pestilent disease.</cd> <au>Shak.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murrain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Murrain
<hw>Mur"rain</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having, or afflicted with,
